hu-RWS5WFMaErqqn-UQ3OuRsQeG9o5ZgZgI-tQdaoL0mKuw-QX7vx1v068boOIIWIQeKV3RjwEVS01QXp53qRq-aajjTPcPSPfte0-_quDYMExQU0tSr2zWH6GgyVhk8yfRLrxuLzsf564dMoVHRfn2dwrg-ejKDFnNaTQ41-Q7w-VfSJGROTDT-q_VuwmL0b3QU6FgZ9adqEOD3eKK9E-X-u5g_URyY2BOrmv6HqIhHoic4r5V5QKc8DSrBsVcyVmehuW6es4ou2Ju628cJ2GtZSRUVwk-QesZUxZCa6DZUoH1vAwNDS7bD1VqVYNI5gIvYRoGXD5cwkWQ9JwW1k301KZirOriGg3Dd_6aI1LhfG80H7ymdArhgafoE2YlR\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining SSL and Docker**\\n\\nI'm reflecting on the use of JDK SSL for TLS and X509Token coverage. While this approach can be effective, I’m facing issues with the native-image run failing. There’s also the possibility that optional WildFly might complicate matters. I need to ensure that any risk notes are included in my considerations. And, oh, I have to remember to mention that Docker should not be a part of this discussion!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"JGroups is mostly self-contained and does not need Docker or external services, but reliable meaningful tests should force loopback/IPv4 networking; SLF4J is an optional integration worth adding if logging paths are covered.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.slf4j:slf4j-api:1.7.31\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"JGroups 5.2.2.Final declares SLF4J as an optional logging dependency and LogFactory selects SLF4J when present; existing JGroups tests in this repository also include it to exercise logging integration without requiring Log4J2.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set `jgroups.bind_addr=127.0.0.1` and `java.net.preferIPv4Stack=true` for JVM tests and native runtime arguments. Prefer `SHARED_LOOPBACK`/`SHARED_LOOPBACK_PING` or `Util.getTestStack(...)` for channels instead of default UDP multicast stacks. Avoid requiring real JDBC, DNS, Kubernetes, or multicast infrastructure; use in-memory/stub drivers or loopback stacks when covering protocols such as `JDBC_PING`.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"JGroups supports discovery protocols backed by databases, DNS, Kubernetes, shared files, and multicast, but those are optional deployment modes and should not be introduced as hard test infrastructure unless a specific failing path requires them.\",\n    \"JGroups can optionally probe WildFly OpenSSL via `org.wildfly.openssl`, but TLS coverage can use the JDK SSL provider; adding WildFly OpenSSL may introduce native-provider behavior and should be done only if the failing path specifically requires that branch.\",\n    \"If tests instantiate default `JChannel` stacks without loopback/IPv4 setup, CI and native-image runs may be flaky or fail due host network, multicast, or IPv6 differences.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e6eccc4300dd01f016a42602949ac8190bbde6b59f7587c6d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2623, "output": 1465, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53752, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782734869775, "responseId": "resp_0e6eccc4300dd01f016a4260167acc8190a86839e916463c0f"}, "toolResults": []}
